교재 및 참고문헌: Macroeconomics/Jones, Charles I. (Charles Irving)/W.W. Norton & Company/2018 / 4th ed
There is NO main textbook while my lecture is based on the following textbooks:
1.Gregory Mankiw, Macroeconomics, 9th edition, Worth Publishers, 2015 (only Korean edition is available)
3.Stephen Williamson, Macroeconomics, after 5th edition, Addison Wesley, 2013
4.Charles I. Jones, Macroeconomics, after 3rd edition, Norton, 2014

For instance, lectures on Keynesian model will be mainly based on Blanchard, Mankiw, and Jones while lectures on Neo-classical models will be mainly based on Williamson. Growth theories can be further studied by choosing any of the above textbooks.

I do not have a main textbook since none of the existing macro textbooks are perfect. Usually they take one particular view while ignore the other view although none of the theories are perfect. I do not like this approach. Hence, I do not require you to purchase all of the textbooks though I encourage you to get at least one of them for further study. It is not a problem at all even you do not have any of the recommended textbooks. If a student wants to read a textbook written in Korean, I recommend the textbook (1) co-authored by Prof. Jangok Cho and Prof. Chul-In Lee and (2) Prof. Woonchan Jung and Prof. Youngsik Kim.

In order to enhance students' understanding on the materials, a brief (not full!) lecture note will be provided. It contains key concepts and ideas that you will learn throughout the lectures but does not contain detailed explanations.
I further recommend reading various articles from WSJ, Economist, NY Times and etc; whenever necessary, I will provide articles as a further reading.
